<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 7:27PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...Showers with strong wind gusts will impact portions of southern
Wheeler, Collingsworth and eastern Donley Counties through 800 PM
CDT...
At 724 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking showers along a line
extending from 3 miles west of Dozier to 6 miles south of Quail to
15 miles south of Memphis. Movement was northeast at 45 mph. These
showers have had a history of strong wind gusts.
HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wellington, Shamrock, Dodson, Lutie, Dozier, Samnorwood and Quail.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...55 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
